# Day 5 – Windows Security Basics (Cybersecurity Prep)

## Event Viewer
- Used to view system, application, and security events.
- Security logs show authentication attempts and account actions.

## Important Event IDs
- 4624 – Successful login
- 4625 – Failed login (brute-force indicator)
- 4672 – Admin privilege login (high risk)

## Task Manager
- Shows running processes and performance usage.
- Useful for spotting suspicious high-CPU malware-like processes.

## Services
- Background system functions. Attackers may stop security services.

## Local Users & Groups
- Contains user accounts and permission groups.
- Attackers may create hidden administrative accounts.

---

These notes help track Windows security fundamentals used in SOC analysis.
